04/10/2007
THE HAGUE, Netherlands -- Bulgaria became a member of the European Police Office (Europol) at a ceremony in The Hague on Wednesday (October 3rd). 
Last year, Bulgaria and Europol exchanged information on 780 occasions; that number has already doubled this year. 
Europol Director Max Peter Ratzel said Bulgaria has been submitting more and more essential and accurate information, making it a desired member of the agency. 
(BNT, Actualno.com, Darik - 04/10/07; BTA - 03/10/07)
